Biography

Two-sport standout in soccer and lacrosse … a three-year starter in both sports.

2018

Appeared in all 17 matches, starting 16 … had a goal for 2 points, with 11 shots … scored goal in 3-0 win over Clarion … in lacrosse, started all 17 matches … finished third on the team in scoring with 18 goals and 5 assists for 23 points … led team with 20 caused turnovers and was second in ground balls with 38.

2017

Two-sport standout in soccer and lacrosse … played in all 17 matches, with 16 starts, in soccer … had one goal and one assist … lone goal was the game-winner against California(Pa.) … assisted on a goal against Pitt-Johnstown … in lacrosse, started 15 contests while playing in all 16 … finished with 5 goals and 3 assists for 8 points … was second on the team with 38 draw controls.

2016

Played in all 19 matches, with nine starts, including the final eight matches … scored one goal, the game-winner in a 1-0 win over California(Pa.) … also played a key role on the women’s lacrosse team in the spring, appearing in all 17 matches, with 10 starts … finished with a goal and 5 assists for 6 points.

HIGH SCHOOL

A standout in both women’s soccer and women’s lacrosse at Bishop Grimes High School, also attending CBA … ended up being a three-year starter in soccer, along with two years in lacrosse and bowling, and competing a year in track & field … Bishop Grimes won the women’s soccer conference championships her junior and senior years, reaching the New York state sectional semifinals as a junior … earned first team All-New York honors as a senior and was an honorable mention selection as a sophomore … in lacrosse, was a second team All-New York honoree as a senior and an honorable mention selection as a junior … in bowling, finished third at sectional tournament.

PERSONAL

Born April 29, 1998 … Biology major with a minor in Chemistry … has a 3.46 GPA … daughter of Margaret and Noel Dobbins … has one sister, Hailey, who played lacrosse at Syracuse, and this past year at Cortland State, where she was an All-American and conference Defender of the Year..
